      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_fw_download_1a9bb661eb7e96c9043e0960d3a01af6a8" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="virtual">
        <type><ref refid="class_fw_fsm_1a281f4c9dd77f0f9e7b08c7609dcbfffe" kindref="member">FwFsm::StateId</ref></type>
        <definition>FwFsm::StateId handle_DlFailed</definition>
        <argsstring>(PoolElem **pElem)</argsstring>
        <name>handle_DlFailed</name>
        <reimplements refid="class_fw_state_1a9bb661eb7e96c9043e0960d3a01af6a8">handle_DlFailed</reimplements>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="class_pool_elem" kindref="compound">PoolElem</ref> **</type>
          <declname>pElem</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Firmware download state handler function for DlFailed events. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>pElem</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to pointer to message of type <ref refid="class_pool_elem" kindref="compound">PoolElem</ref></para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Returns the state ID of the idle state or eNoChange</para>
</simplesect>
The function checks if the maximum number of retries has not been reached. In this case the function start the retry timer by calling function startRetryTimer of the <ref refid="class_fw_upd_ctrl" kindref="compound">FwUpdCtrl</ref> class instance to schedule a firmware download retry and returns the state ID eNoChange. If the maximum number of retries has been reached the retry counter will be set to 0 and the DlFailed message will be forwarded to MQTT connector task. Afterwards the function performes a delay of 2 seconds to let other tasks take over process, before it performes a reset. Returning to the state ID eIdle will never be reached. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
