      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_fw_download_1a22de52c28e140efcdb90423ce29714eb" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="virtual">
        <type><ref refid="class_fw_fsm_1a281f4c9dd77f0f9e7b08c7609dcbfffe" kindref="member">FwFsm::StateId</ref></type>
        <definition>FwFsm::StateId handle_timer_exp</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>handle_timer_exp</name>
        <reimplements refid="class_fw_state_1a22de52c28e140efcdb90423ce29714eb">handle_timer_exp</reimplements>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Firmware download state handler function for timer expired events. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="return"><para>The state ID eNoChange</para>
</simplesect>
The function calculated the time difference from the download start time to the current time. If the time difference is more than maxDownloadDelay or if the maximum number of retries has been reached the download will be expected as failed and message eFwDlFailed will be send to MQTT connector task with error CODE3 and after a delay of 2 seconds a reset will be performed. <linebreak/>
Otherwise a new download attempt will be started by calling the method requestDownload of the <ref refid="class_fw_upd_ctrl" kindref="compound">FwUpdCtrl</ref> class instance. Pointer variable pd is assigned to <ref refid="class_fw_upd_ctrl" kindref="compound">FwUpdCtrl</ref> class instance. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
